<TEXT>
machine guntoting guerrillas some in 
dresses for lack of other clothes cruise the streets of liberias 
secondlargest city in stolen pickup trucks waiting for the order 
to invade the capital 
they are biding their time confident they can defeat government 
troops and force out or kill president samuel doe 
buchanan a port city 90 miles southeast of the capital of 
monrovia and the countrys industrial center is at a standstill 
trains that carry iron ore timber and rubber are idle and no 
ships call to take deliveries 
it is a city of rusting corrugated tin shanties and homes burned 
by government soldiers who were chased out by rebels of the 
national patriotic front 
no stores are open and gasoline is almost gone at the only 
station in town where there is any rebels pas the day dropping 
soda bottles down tubes to fish out fuel little by little 
the rebels led by former doe aide charles taylor invaded 
liberia on dec 24 they reached buchanan on may 19 and after a 
week of heavy fighting and scores of deaths they finally won 
control of the city 
other rebels are within 15 miles of monrovia and leaders say 
all of their forces are poised to storm the capital 
peace talks between the government and the rebels were to resume 
monday in neighboring sierra leone and the leader of the 
government delegation said he expected a settlement 
we have come to make peace and that is going to happen 
information minister emmanuel bowier said sunday 
but the rebels say doe must step down for any settlement 
if he decides to stay we will fight and we know who will die 
and who will live said one commando wearing grenades bullets 
and a headband of seashells who called himself rebel 60 
he patrolled buchanans streets with four other rebels and two 
goats in the back of his pickup a government soldiers skull was 
tied to the front of the commandeered truck 
amos kanga 27 sang to himself as he carried a skull down a 
dirt road toward a rebel checkpoint outside buchanan he was taking 
it back to decorate his guard post 
it will be shining come back and see he said with a grin 
the rebels are a motley ragtag force who arm and clothe 
themselves with anything they can capture or steal 
buchanan residents remember rebels directing gunfire at liberian 
army positions while other insurgents stood by and tried on pants 
looted from local residences 
many wear torn filthy clothes some sport colored ski goggles 
huge stereo headphones connected to nothing bright orange life 
vests garish womens wigs dresses and even rubber halloween 
masks 
theyre like teenage mutant ninja rebels says one 
foreigner in buchanan referring to the turtle warrior cartoon 
characters 
alhough the rebels are unruly they are by most accounts far 
less brutal than the government troops 
one foreigner who has stayed in buchanan told of how government 
troops shot out windows and blasted through the door of his house 
where about 30 of his firms employees had taken refuge 
they burst in and demanded if were harboring rebels said 
the foreigner who spoke on condition of anonymity they didnt 
find any so they took 2000 instead 
such belligerence has left residents edgy im afraid to go 
out said a 26yearold liberian woman who lives just outside 
buchanan anytime someone just says hey my heart jumps 
the army has been accused of atrocities but taylors forces 
have been accused of random violence as well 
johnny konoh 28 a hospital orderly says he was shot june 1 by 
a rebel soldier while he was wearing his blueandwhite uniform 
with a red cross on the chest 
the rebel threatened to kill him then shot him twice one shot 
hit a shoulder and the other grazed his face disfiguring an eye 
nothing have i done to him konoh said i dont know why 
sporadic fighting has continued for weeks at the 
bridgestonefirestone rubber plantation about 35 miles by road 
from monrovia and next to the nations international airport 
moses blah leading a rebel patrol at the plantation repeated 
taylors claim that the rebels can take monrovia in 12 hours 
we are trained in guerrilla fighting and commando naval 
fighting and city fighting he said we can even fight in the 
city of new york 
