union militant jeanmarie montes was killed in the attack and 
villard and political activist emmanuel mani were wounded 
president ertha pascaltrouillot was to meet with the council 
today the independent radio antilles said the council held an 
emergency meeting with army officials sunday in the national palace 
today and tuesday flags were flying at halfstaff and cinemas 
and other places of amusement were asked to close state offices 
and commercial businesses were to be open however 
villard a prominent businessman was a leading opponent of the 
29year dictatorship of the duvalier family which ended in 1986 
villard authored article 291 of the constitution which banned 
known supporters of the duvaliers from running for public office 
