<DOCNO> AP900625-0074 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
here is a chronology of major events in the nancy cruzan 
righttodie case 
jan 11 1983 nancy cruzan then 25 has a car wreck on a 
country road southeast of carthage mo in the ozarks of southwest 
missouri thrown from the car she is first thought to be dead 
paramedics restart her breathing but her brain is without oxygen 
for so long that she never regains consciousness 
feb 5 1983 doctors surgically implant a feeding tube in ms 
cruzans stomach at a time when her prognosis is uncertain 
through it she receives food and water to keep her alive she 
isnt on any life support system such as a respirator 
oct 19 1983 ms cruzan is moved to the missouri 
rehabilitation center in mount vernon where she remains her 
parents joe and joyce cruzan of carterville mo visit her on a 
regular basis 
oct 23 1987 the cruzans ask jasper county circuit court for 
a judgment on their request that they be allowed to have ms 
cruzans feeding tube removed so their daughter can die as they 
believe she would want 
march 9 1988 a threeday hearing begins on the familys 
request the cruzans say their daughter has a commonlaw right to 
be free from unwanted medical treatment and state and federal 
constitutional rights to privacy that protects her right to refuse 
unwanted medical treatment 
july 27 1988 jasper county circuit judge charles teel jr 
issues a judgment authorizing the cruzans acting as nancys legal 
guardians to request the withholding of food and water from their 
daughter 
aug 3 1988 missouri attorney general william webster files 
notice to the circuit court that the state will appeal the ruling 
to the missouri supreme court 
sept 29 1988 the missouri supreme court hears arguments in 
the case with ms cruzans family watching in the courtroom 
nov 16 1988 in a 43 decision the missouri supreme court 
overturns the lower court holding there is no legal authority to 
grant the cruzans request the family then appeals to the us 
supreme court 
dec 6 1989 the nations highest court hears arguments in 
the cruzan case its the first righttodie case that the court 
has considered 
june 25 1990 the us supreme court bars the removal of a 
lifesustaining tube from ms cruzan 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

