given the courts recent decisions 
we were i guess hopeful mainly because the decision was 
obviously so important to the family its hard not to be hopeful 
under those circumstances he said 
but when we looked at it realistically and with the recent 
history of the court this is not that surprising he said 
for joe cruzan a sheet metal worker from carterville theres 
no doubt about what his daughter would have wanted 
she would say pull the plug stop it i dont want to live 
like this i have no dignity cruzan said in an interview last 
year 
