<TEXT>
a public inquiry into the bombing of 
pan am flight 103 will begin oct 1 officials said monday but 
relatives of the victims were not satisfied 
all 259 people aboard the boeing 747 and 11 people in the town 
of lockerbie were killed when the aircraft exploded and crashed on 
dec 21 1988 
lord fraser scotlands chief law officer said in december he 
would convene a fatal accident inquiry but he did not announce the 
date until monday 
relatives groups have been demanding a broader inquiry 
independent of the government 
dr jim swire who heads a relatives group called uk families 
flight 103 said he doubted the value of a fatal accident inquiry 
we believe there is a coverup of uk security and until 
there is a full independent inquiry we will continue to believe 
so said swire whose daughter flora 24 was killed on the plane 
scottish and us officials have said they do not have enough 
evidence to prosecute anyone for the attack 
the ordering of the fatal accident inquiry does not in any way 
signify an end of the hunt for those responsible for the mass 
murder at lockerbie said fraser we remain as committed today 
as ever to bringing the evil perpetrators to justice he said 
frasers comments indicated he did not expect a criminal inquiry 
by oct 1 
the fatal accident inquiry will be held at crichton royal 
hospital in dumfries about 10 miles west of lockerbie 
scottish police who have coordinated an international 
investigation have said the bomb was hidden inside a 
radiocassette recorder that was probably put aboard the flight in 
frankfurt west germany 
baggage was shifted to the 747 at heathrow airport in london 
and the bomb exploded as the new yorkbound flight was reaching 
cruising altitude 
the fatal accident inquiry will be conducted by sheriff 
principal john mowatt the senior sheriff for southwestern scotland 
the sheriff sets the scope for the inquiry he is charged with 
finding where and when the deaths occurred the cause any 
reasonable precautions that might have avoided it any defects 
in systems or procedures that contributed to the deaths and any 
other facts relevant to the circumstances 
frasers office said a sheriff had the power to compel witnesses 
to attend or documents to be produced but this power is confined 
to the united kingdom sheriffs can issue a letter of request 
to overseas authorities for evidence to be made available 
the government may claim public interest immunity over 
documents exhibits or evidence but that claim may be overturned 
by courts 
