engineers at rockwell international corp in downey calif failed 
to find a leak in hydrogen lines that had been removed from 
columbias external tank 
that confirmed nasas suspicion the problem was with plumbing on 
the orbiter side 
columbias 17inchdiameter disconnect valve in a pipe that 
carries liquid hydrogen from the external tank to the main engines 
will be removed and replaced with the one from endeavour endeavour 
is under construction by rockwell and is not scheduled to fly until 
1992 
only one valve was built for each shuttle there are no spares 
columbias bad valve will be shipped to california for testing 
replacing the valve on the orbiter side is going to take the 
most time said lisa malone spokeswoman for the national 
aeronautics and space administration nonetheless the astronomy 
mission remains targeted for midaugust she said 
columbias scheduled may 30 launch with the 150 million astro 
