pad on thursday partly filling the shuttles external tank with 
supercold liquid hydrogen to make sure there are no leaks the 
same test was conducted with columbia a week after the scrubbed 
launch and replicated the leak 
prelaunch tests for leaks normally are conducted with a gaseous 
helium at room temperature rather than volatile liquid hydrogen 
chilled to minus 420 degrees 
