the family of nancy cruzan who has lain 
in a comalike condition for seven years said monday they will not 
waver in their desire to let her die with dignity 
joe and joyce cruzan released a statement at a news conference 
in kansas city following a us supreme court ruling that barred 
them from removing a lifesustaining feeding tube 
the cruzans did not say anything about the ruling but restated 
their feelings about their 32yearold daughter who was injured in 
a 1983 auto accident and has neither spoken nor acknowledged their 
voices since 
the decision to stop treatment and allow a loved one to die is 
one of the most difficult decisions a family can face the 
cruzans statement said however because of our lifelong shared 
love with nancy and our understanding of her values we concluded 
that we had no choice but to try to set her free from this hopeless 
condition she is trapped in not to do so would be to disregard the 
very meaning of nancys lived life 
