<TEXT>
the pentagon and congress have reached a 
compromise over a requirement that the department maintain some of 
the sr71 blackbird spy planes for use in a national crisis 
according to a letter released monday 
the air force and congress agreed last year to terminate the top 
secret program opting instead for satellites that could provide 
the same intelligence information for less money 
but in report language accompanying a 4 billion spending bill 
president bush signed last month lawmakers called on the pentagon 
to maintain the aircraft by tail numbers so that flight 
operations could begin within 90 days of an emergency 
defense secretary dick cheney criticized the provision which 
though nonbinding would do serious damage to the relationship 
between congress and the pentagon if the department ignored it 
the air force and congressional committees negotiated a 
compromise that cheney detailed in a june 21 letter to sen robert 
c byrd dwva chairman of the senate appropriations committee 
we will place three sr71a aircraft and six associated 
reconnaissance sensors and electronic countermeasure suites into 
longterm storage as a hedge against a protracted conflict some 
time in the future cheney said in the letter 
the time it will take and the cost of restoring these stored 
aircraft and sensors to a condition that would support safe 
operations will depend on the length of the storage period 
the defense secretary also said the pentagon will make trainer 
aircraft two sr71a aircraft flight simulator and all associated 
sr71 spares and support equipment available for loan or transfer 
to nasa 
the space agency according to a memorandum from cheney to air 
force secretary donald rice would assume the cost for operating 
and maintaining the aircraft and parts 
no estimate was included in the letter 
cheney said reconnaissance operations involving the black 
daggershaped planes could not resume in a safe manner on 
90day notice he also noted that maintenance crews air crews and 
other personnel with skills to operate and care for the blackbird 
are gone 
we no longer have an sr71 flight capability cheney said 
during more than two decades of service the blackbird regularly 
flew missions over heavily defended north vietnam and provided 
intelligence in many other regions including the middle east 
china and the persian gulf 
the plane can outrun the fastest fighters and has never been 
shot down 
in march in a flight marking its retirement a blackbird set a 
record for a coasttocoast flight flying from los angeles to 
washington dc in 68 minutes 17 seconds 
