about 400 inmates rioted at the states 
minimum security prison monday looting and setting two buildings 
ablaze and ripping doors off hinges a guard was injured by a 
thrown rock authorities said 
the disturbance at the carl robinson correctional institution 
started about 715 am when the inmates refused to return to their 
dormitories after breakfast to protest the food and low wages for 
their prison jobs said correction department spokesman william 
wheeler 
the inmates threw rocks broke windows and broke into the two 
buildings which housed mess halls a commissary and a gymnasium 
wheeler said 
the inmates looted the commissary and torched both buildings 
which were reduced to rubble wheeler estimated the damage at 27 
million 
about 250 correction officers including scores brought in from 
other state prisons used tear gas to quell the riot 
most of the inmates were returned to their dormitories by 1230 
pm and warden george bronson said preliminary checks showed all 
1356 inmates accounted for 
the perimeter security was maintained throughout the entire 
incident bronson said the correction officers were in 
control the inmates were in the yard 
he said the riot instigators would be charged 
a guard suffered a broken ankle from a rock thrown by an inmate 
wheeler said and a number of inmates complained of injuries like 
smoke inhalation and cuts and bruises 
about 100 state troopers equipped with riot gear and police dogs 
were brought in but remained on standby about a quarter mile away 
wheeler said 
