of abortions for minors for example the court in 1979 said states 
may require a pregnant unmarried minor to obtain parental consent 
to an abortion so long as a judicial bypass option is provided 
twentytwo states have enacted such parentalconsent laws ten 
states have enacted parentalnotification laws similar to those 
ruled on monday 
