tuesday 
earlier community officials announced the european leaders had 
agreed to start a conference on political union dec 14 those 
talks will run parallel to talks on economic and monetary union 
beginning dec 15 
today we entered into a decisive phase in the construction of 
europe frances foreign minister roland dumas told reporters 
thatcher went along with the agreement despite her opposition 
to the proposal for economic union that calls for a single european 
currency and central bank 
british officials quoted her as saying a single currency would 
rob member states of fundamental control over their economies 
britain is expected to suggest a compromise setting up a new 
currency to circulate alongside existing currencies for perhaps 
another 20 years 
the agreement to hold the december conferences had been widely 
expected after britain said it would not try to block it 
on south african sanctions britain said it would not press for 
bans on imports of south african iron steel and gold coins 
jointly imposed by the community in 1986 to be lifted now 
some obsevers regarded this as tacit acknowledgement that mrs 
thatcher would have a tough time getting a decision while black 
leader nelson mandela is in the united states pressing for 
sanctions to be maintained until apartheid is abolished 
