addition caterpillar sold 382 million worth of products made in 
latin america 
other factors contributing to caterpillars profit decline 
include tight us monetary policies and higher inflation stober 
said also a costly plant modernization program is taking longer 
than expected and costing more than projected 
caterpillar says that with no further deterioration in the world 
economy and a more stable economy in brazil its profits are 
expected to improve in 1991 
