aig the largest us underwriter of commercial and industrial 
insurance also will provide ilfc with 125 million in financing as 
part of the deal 
analysts and spokesmen said the deal gives ilfc financial muscle 
at a time when the leasing outfit must borrow heavily to complete 
an ambitious expansion 
theyve found someone with lots of cash low cost of funds 
and willing to take some greater risk in return for greater 
rewards said daniel a hersch a securities analyst with bateman 
eichler hill richards inc in los angeles 
ilfc one of the worlds biggest aircraft leasing companies 
owns 98 jetliners worth more than 3 billion and averaging only 
three years of age 
it has placed 10 billion worth of firm orders for planes to be 
delivered over 10 years and has another 4 billion in options 
that means ilfc which already has had to borrow heavily and 
occasionally issue new stock to finance its deals will need much 
more capital at a time when it is harder to come by 
i think that having a strategic alliance with a backer of the 
stature and creditworthiness of aig should instill a greater 
confidence in the financial markets jay jacobsen a spokesman 
for ilfc said in a telephone interview from new york 
ilfc will continue to borrow in the markets to raise capital 
jacobsen said aigs triplea debt rating the highest ranking 
possible will enable ilfc to borrow funds more cheaply 
